You said

you are a p5js devloper, write a simple p5js app that simulates a slotcar track, 2 cars, 2 controllers, controlled from keyboard, ask for 1 or 2 players, have autonomus player against human if 1 is selected. keep in mind, slot cars, and there are basically fast, slow, stop commands.

Gemini said

Hello! Let's get this race started. As a p5.js developer, I love this concept because it focuses on momentum and constraints‚Äîthe essence of slot car racing.

In a slot car sim, the "challenge" isn't steering; it's managing speed so you don't fly off the curves (though for this simple version, we'll focus on the movement mechanics).

The Track Logic

Since slot cars follow a fixed rail, we‚Äôll use a simple elliptical path.

  • Player 1: Uses the 'W' key.

  • Player 2 / AI: Uses the 'UP_ARROW' key.

The Code

JavaScript
let gameState = "START"; // START, PLAY
let numPlayers = 1;

let trackX, trackY, trackW, trackH;
let cars = [];

function setup() {
  createCanvas(800, 600);
  trackX = width / 2;
  trackY = height / 2;
  trackW = 600;
  trackH = 400;

  // Initialize two cars (lane offset, color, isAI)
  cars.push(new SlotCar(0, color(255, 50, 50), false)); // Player 1
  cars.push(new SlotCar(40, color(50, 50, 255), true)); // Player 2 or AI
}

function draw() {
  background(40);

  if (gameState === "START") {
    drawStartScreen();
  } else {
    drawTrack();
    
    cars.forEach((car, index) => {
      car.update(index === 1 && numPlayers === 1); // Pass AI flag
      car.display();
    });
    
    drawUI();
  }
}

function drawTrack() {
  noFill();
  strokeWeight(15);
  stroke(100);
  ellipse(trackX, trackY, trackW, trackH); // Outer Lane
  ellipse(trackX, trackY, trackW - 80, trackH - 80); // Inner Lane
}

class SlotCar {
  constructor(offset, col, canBeAI) {
    this.angle = 0;
    this.speed = 0;
    this.maxSpeed = 0.05;
    this.friction = 0.98;
    this.accel = 0.002;
    this.offset = offset;
    this.col = col;
    this.canBeAI = canBeAI;
  }

  update(isAuton) {
    let driving = false;

    if (isAuton) {
      // Simple AI logic: try to maintain a steady fast speed
      if (this.speed < 0.03) driving = true;
    } else {
      // Manual Control
      if (this.canBeAI) {
        if (keyIsDown(UP_ARROW)) driving = true;
      } else {
        if (keyIsDown(87)) driving = true; // 'W' key
      }
    }

    if (driving) {
      this.speed += this.accel;
    } else {
      this.speed *= this.friction;
    }

    this.speed = constrain(this.speed, 0, this.maxSpeed);
    this.angle += this.speed;
  }

  display() {
    let rX = (trackW - this.offset) / 2;
    let rY = (trackH - this.offset) / 2;
    let x = trackX + cos(this.angle) * rX;
    let y = trackY + sin(this.angle) * rY;

    push();
    translate(x, y);
    rotate(this.angle + HALF_PI);
    fill(this.col);
    noStroke();
    rectMode(CENTER);
    rect(0, 0, 20, 40, 5); // Car body
    fill(255, 200);
    rect(0, -10, 15, 10); // Windshield
    pop();
  }
}

function drawStartScreen() {
  fill(255);
  textAlign(CENTER);
  textSize(32);
  text("SLOT CAR CHAMPIONSHIP", width / 2, height / 2 - 40);
  textSize(20);
  text("Press '1' for Single Player (vs AI)\nPress '2' for Two Players", width / 2, height / 2 + 20);
}

function drawUI() {
  fill(255);
  textSize(16);
  textAlign(LEFT);
  text("P1: Hold 'W'", 20, 30);
  if (numPlayers === 2) {
    text("P2: Hold 'UP ARROW'", 20, 55);
  } else {
    text("P2: AUTONOMOUS MODE", 20, 55);
  }
}

function keyPressed() {
  if (gameState === "START") {
    if (key === '1') {
      numPlayers = 1;
      gameState = "PLAY";
    } else if (key === '2') {
      numPlayers = 2;
      cars[1].canBeAI = true; // Set to controllable
      gameState = "PLAY";
    }
  }
}

How it works:

  • The Slot: The cars calculate their x,y position using polar coordinates (rcos(Œ∏),rsin(Œ∏)). This ensures they never leave the track, perfectly mimicking the "pin" in a slot car.

  • Physics: I added a friction variable. If you let go of the key, the car coasts to a stop rather than freezing instantly, which feels much more natural.

  • AI: The autonomous player is programmed with a "target speed." It taps the throttle whenever it drops below a certain threshold, making it a consistent opponent to beat.

design a typical f1 track.

Gemini said

Designing a Formula 1 track is a delicate balance between high-speed thrill, heavy braking zones (for overtaking), and technical safety. To create a "typical" modern circuit‚Äîoften referred to as a "Tilke-drome" after famous designer Hermann Tilke‚Äîwe need to incorporate specific sectors that test different aspects of a car's performance.

The Anatomy of an F1 Track

1. The Main Straight & Turn 1

The main straight is the heart of the track. It hosts the starting grid and the primary DRS (Drag Reduction System) zone.

  • The Design: It usually ends in a "heavy braking" zone‚Äîa sharp 90-degree or hairpin turn.

  • The Purpose: This forces cars from 330 km/h down to 80 km/h, creating the best opportunity for overtaking at the start of the race.

2. Sector 1: High-Speed Flow

Following the first corner, a typical track features a series of sweeping "S" curves (think Silverstone‚Äôs Maggotts and Becketts or Suzuka‚Äôs Esses).

  • The Design: Fluid, rhythmic turns that require high downforce.

  • The Physics: Drivers maintain high speeds here, putting immense lateral G-force on their necks and testing the car's aerodynamic balance.

3. Sector 2: The Technical Back-Straight

This middle section often contains the longest straight on the circuit, sometimes featuring a slight kink or curve.

  • The Design: A long, flat-out stretch followed by a tight chicane.

  • The Purpose: It tests engine power and top-end speed. The chicane at the end prevents the cars from carrying too much speed into the final, more technical sector.

4. Sector 3: The Slow & Twistie

The final sector is usually low-speed and highly technical to keep the cars close together before they hit the main straight again.

  • The Design: 90-degree turns and a "stadium section" where grandstands are packed close to the track.

  • The Exit: The final corner is crucial; it must be designed so that a trailing car can stay close to the leader‚Äôs gearbox to pick up a "slipstream" for the main straight.

Technical Specifications

FeatureDescription
Track LengthTypically between 5km and 7km.
Track WidthUsually 12m to 15m to allow for side-by-side racing.
Run-off AreasMix of gravel traps (to punish mistakes) and asphalt (for safety).
Pit LaneParallel to the main straight, requiring a speed limiter (usually 80 km/h).

A Quick Tip for your p5.js App:

If you want to translate this into your code, you can move beyond a simple ellipse by using Bezier curves (bezier()) or Vertices (beginShape()). This would allow you to create a "straight-away" followed by a tight "hairpin" to make your slot car simulation much more challenging!

Gemini said

Here is the complete, single-file p5.js sketch. I have upgraded the track from a simple circle to a Formula 1-style layout using a custom path, and updated the cars to handle more complex geometry.

JavaScript
/** * SLOT CAR F1 SIMULATOR
 * Controls: 
 * P1: 'W' key
 * P2: 'UP_ARROW' key (or AI mode)
 */

let gameState = "START";
let numPlayers = 1;
let trackPoints = [];
let car1, car2;

function setup() {
  createCanvas(800, 600);
  
  // Define a typical F1 "Tilke-style" track layout
  // These are normalized coordinates that we will scale to the canvas
  let rawPoints = [
    {x: 100, y: 500}, // Start/Finish Straight
    {x: 600, y: 500}, // Heavy Braking Turn 1
    {x: 700, y: 400}, 
    {x: 600, y: 300}, // Sector 1 S-Curves
    {x: 700, y: 200},
    {x: 500, y: 100}, // Top Straight
    {x: 200, y: 100}, // Tight Hairpin
    {x: 100, y: 250}, // Technical Infield
    {x: 300, y: 300},
    {x: 100, y: 400}  // Final Corner
  ];

  // Interpolate points to create a smooth continuous "slot"
  for (let i = 0; i < rawPoints.length; i++) {
    let p1 = rawPoints[i];
    let p2 = rawPoints[(i + 1) % rawPoints.length];
    for (let t = 0; t < 0.1; t += 0.005) {
      let x = lerp(p1.x, p2.x, t);
      let y = lerp(p1.y, p2.y, t);
      // We use curve tightness later, but for a slot car, 
      // simple linear segments between many points works best
    }
  }
  
  // Store the track path points
  trackPoints = rawPoints;

  // Initialize cars (color, key, isAI)
  car1 = new SlotCar(color(255, 50, 50), 87, false, 0);       // 'W'
  car2 = new SlotCar(color(50, 150, 255), UP_ARROW, true, 15); // 'UP' or AI
}

function draw() {
  background(30);

  if (gameState === "START") {
    drawStartScreen();
  } else {
    drawTrack();
    
    car1.update(false);
    car2.update(numPlayers === 1); // car2 is AI if 1 player selected
    
    car1.display();
    car2.display();
    
    drawUI();
  }
}

function drawTrack() {
  // Draw the asphalt
  noFill();
  stroke(60);
  strokeWeight(40);
  beginShape();
  for (let p of trackPoints) {
    curveVertex(p.x, p.y);
  }
  endShape(CLOSE);

  // Draw the center "Slot" rail
  stroke(150, 150, 0);
  strokeWeight(2);
  beginShape();
  for (let p of trackPoints) {
    curveVertex(p.x, p.y);
  }
  endShape(CLOSE);
  
  // Draw Start/Finish line
  stroke(255);
  strokeWeight(4);
  line(150, 480, 150, 520);
}

class SlotCar {
  constructor(col, controlKey, canBeAI, offset) {
    this.col = col;
    this.key = controlKey;
    this.isAI = canBeAI;
    this.offset = offset; // Visual offset so cars don't overlap perfectly
    
    this.progress = 0; // 0 to 1 along the track
    this.speed = 0;
    this.maxSpeed = 0.005;
    this.accel = 0.0001;
    this.friction = 0.97;
  }

  update(activeAI) {
    let isAccelerating = false;

    if (activeAI) {
      // AI logic: maintain a brisk but safe pace
      if (this.speed < 0.0035) isAccelerating = true;
    } else {
      if (keyIsDown(this.key)) isAccelerating = true;
    }

    if (isAccelerating) {
      this.speed += this.accel;
    } else {
      this.speed *= this.friction;
    }

    this.speed = constrain(this.speed, 0, this.maxSpeed);
    this.progress += this.speed;
    
    // Loop around the track
    if (this.progress > 1) this.progress = 0;
  }

  display() {
    // Calculate position on the Catmull-Rom spline
    let pos = this.getPointAt(this.progress);
    let nextPos = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.001);
    
    let angle = atan2(nextPos.y - pos.y, nextPos.x - pos.x);

    push();
    translate(pos.x, pos.y);
    rotate(angle);
    
    // Draw Car
    rectMode(CENTER);
    // Shadow
    fill(0, 50);
    rect(2, 2 + this.offset/4, 25, 12, 3);
    // Body
    fill(this.col);
    rect(0, this.offset/4, 25, 12, 3);
    // Cockpit
    fill(20);
    rect(5, this.offset/4, 8, 8, 2);
    pop();
  }

  // Helper to sample the curve at any percentage (0-1)
  getPointAt(t) {
    t = t % 1;
    let i = floor(t * trackPoints.length);
    let p0 = trackPoints[(i + trackPoints.length - 1) % trackPoints.length];
    let p1 = trackPoints[i];
    let p2 = trackPoints[(i + 1) % trackPoints.length];
    let p3 = trackPoints[(i + 2) % trackPoints.length];
    
    let segmentT = (t * trackPoints.length) - i;
    
    return {
      x: curvePoint(p0.x, p1.x, p2.x, p3.x, segmentT),
      y: curvePoint(p0.y, p1.y, p2.y, p3.y, segmentT)
    };
  }
}

function drawStartScreen() {
  fill(255);
  textAlign(CENTER);
  textSize(40);
  text("GP SLOT CARS", width / 2, height / 2 - 50);
  textSize(20);
  text("Press '1' for Solo vs AI", width / 2, height / 2 + 10);
  text("Press '2' for 2-Player Local", width / 2, height / 2 + 40);
  
  textSize(14);
  fill(150);
  text("P1: W Key | P2: Up Arrow", width / 2, height - 50);
}

function drawUI() {
  fill(255);
  noStroke();
  textAlign(LEFT);
  textSize(16);
  text(numPlayers === 1 ? "P1 vs COMPUTER" : "PLAYER vs PLAYER", 20, 30);
}

function keyPressed() {
  if (gameState === "START") {
    if (key === '1') {
      numPlayers = 1;
      gameState = "PLAY";
    }
    if (key === '2') {
      numPlayers = 2;
      gameState = "PLAY";
    }
  }
}

Gemini said

To give this a professional "Pit Wall" feel, I have integrated the p5.js DOM library. This moves the telemetry (lap times and speeds) out of the canvas and into real-time HTML elements, allowing the race view to remain clean.

I've also added Lap Logic: a car must pass the start/finish line (the transition from 0.99 to 0.01 progress) to trigger a lap increment.

JavaScript
/** * F1 SLOT CARS WITH DOM TELEMETRY
 * P1: 'W' | P2/AI: 'UP_ARROW'
 */

let gameState = "START";
let numPlayers = 1;
let trackPoints = [];
let cars = [];
let telemetryUI = [];

function setup() {
  createCanvas(800, 600);
  
  // F1 Track Nodes
  trackPoints = [
    {x: 150, y: 500}, {x: 650, y: 500}, // Start Straight
    {x: 750, y: 400}, {x: 600, y: 350}, // Sector 1
    {x: 700, y: 200}, {x: 400, y: 100}, // Back Straight
    {x: 100, y: 100}, {x: 150, y: 250}, // Hairpin
    {x: 350, y: 350}, {x: 100, y: 400}  // Final Turn
  ];

  // Initialize Cars
  cars.push(new SlotCar("RED RACER", color(255, 50, 50), 87, false, -10)); 
  cars.push(new SlotCar("BLUE BOLT", color(50, 150, 255), UP_ARROW, true, 10));

  setupDOM();
}

function setupDOM() {
  // Create a container for telemetry
  let container = createDiv('');
  container.style('position', 'absolute');
  container.style('top', '20px');
  container.style('right', '20px');
  container.style('font-family', 'monospace');
  container.style('color', '#fff');
  container.style('background', 'rgba(0,0,0,0.7)');
  container.style('padding', '15px');
  container.style('border-left', '4px solid #e10600'); // F1 Red

  cars.forEach((car, i) => {
    let div = createDiv('');
    div.parent(container);
    div.style('margin-bottom', '15px');
    telemetryUI.push(div);
  });
}

function draw() {
  background(30);

  if (gameState === "START") {
    drawStartScreen();
  } else {
    drawTrack();
    
    cars.forEach((car, i) => {
      let isAI = (i === 1 && numPlayers === 1);
      car.update(isAI);
      car.display();
      updateTelemetry(i);
    });
  }
}

function drawTrack() {
  // Asphalt
  noFill();
  stroke(60);
  strokeWeight(45);
  beginShape();
  for (let p of trackPoints) { curveVertex(p.x, p.y); }
  endShape(CLOSE);

  // The Slot
  stroke(200, 200, 0);
  strokeWeight(2);
  beginShape();
  for (let p of trackPoints) { curveVertex(p.x, p.y); }
  endShape(CLOSE);
  
  // Start/Finish Line
  stroke(255);
  strokeWeight(6);
  line(150, 475, 150, 525);
}

class SlotCar {
  constructor(name, col, controlKey, canBeAI, laneOffset) {
    this.name = name;
    this.col = col;
    this.key = controlKey;
    this.laneOffset = laneOffset;
    
    this.progress = 0;
    this.speed = 0;
    this.topSpeed = 0;
    this.laps = 0;
    this.prevProgress = 0;
    
    this.maxSpeedConst = 0.006;
    this.accel = 0.00015;
    this.friction = 0.98;
  }

  update(activeAI) {
    let driving = activeAI ? (this.speed < 0.0042) : keyIsDown(this.key);

    if (driving) {
      this.speed += this.accel;
    } else {
      this.speed *= this.friction;
    }

    this.speed = constrain(this.speed, 0, this.maxSpeedConst);
    this.progress += this.speed;

    // Track Top Speed (Scaled for display)
    let displaySpeed = floor(this.speed * 50000);
    if (displaySpeed > this.topSpeed) this.topSpeed = displaySpeed;

    // Lap Counting
    if (this.progress >= 1) {
      this.progress = 0;
      this.laps++;
    }
    
    this.prevProgress = this.progress;
  }

  display() {
    let pos = this.getPointAt(this.progress);
    let nextPos = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.001);
    let angle = atan2(nextPos.y - pos.y, nextPos.x - pos.x);

    push();
    translate(pos.x, pos.y);
    rotate(angle);
    
    // Lane Offset (shifting car slightly left/right of center)
    translate(0, this.laneOffset);

    // Car Body
    fill(this.col);
    noStroke();
    rectMode(CENTER);
    rect(0, 0, 28, 14, 3);
    // Aero/Wing
    fill(20);
    rect(-10, 0, 6, 18);
    // Cockpit
    fill(255, 150);
    rect(5, 0, 8, 8, 2);
    pop();
  }

  getPointAt(t) {
    t = t % 1;
    let i = floor(t * trackPoints.length);
    let p0 = trackPoints[(i + trackPoints.length - 1) % trackPoints.length];
    let p1 = trackPoints[i];
    let p2 = trackPoints[(i + 1) % trackPoints.length];
    let p3 = trackPoints[(i + 2) % trackPoints.length];
    let segmentT = (t * trackPoints.length) - i;
    return {
      x: curvePoint(p0.x, p1.x, p2.x, p3.x, segmentT),
      y: curvePoint(p0.y, p1.y, p2.y, p3.y, segmentT)
    };
  }
}

function updateTelemetry(index) {
  let car = cars[index];
  let speedKmh = floor(car.speed * 50000);
  telemetryUI[index].html(`
    <strong style="color:${car.col.toString()}">${car.name}</strong><br>
    LAPS: ${car.laps}<br>
    SPEED: ${speedKmh} km/h<br>
    TOP SPEED: ${car.topSpeed} km/h
  `);
}

function drawStartScreen() {
  fill(255);
  textAlign(CENTER);
  textSize(32);
  text("F1 SLOT CAR SIM", width / 2, height / 2 - 20);
  textSize(18);
  text("1: SOLO VS AI | 2: PVP", width / 2, height / 2 + 20);
}

function keyPressed() {
  if (gameState === "START") {
    if (key === '1') { numPlayers = 1; gameState = "PLAY"; }
    if (key === '2') { numPlayers = 2; gameState = "PLAY"; }
  }
}

UI & Gameplay Features:

  1. DOM Telemetry: On the top right, you'll see a dark-mode F1 style overlay. It displays live speed, lap counts, and the all-important Top Speed record.

  2. Lane Offsets: The cars are now offset from the center rail (one slightly inside, one slightly outside) so they look like they are racing in parallel slots.

  3. F1 Aesthetics: I added a "Rear Wing" and a cockpit to the car shapes and a Start/Finish line to the track.

  4. Scaling: The raw speed values (which are tiny decimals for path progress) are scaled by a factor of 50,000 to give you realistic-looking km/h readings.

add if too fast, then go off the track, slow the vehicle down to a stop, then allow the player to regain control. put the car back on the track.

Gemini said

This adds the "deslotting" mechanic. In real slot car racing, if you carry too much momentum into a curve, the centrifugal force overcomes the guide pin's grip.

I have implemented a Centrifugal Force check:

  1. Detection: It calculates the "sharpness" of the turn by comparing the car's current heading to its next heading.

  2. The Crash: If Speed√óCurvature>Threshold, the car flies off the track.

  3. The Penalty: The car skids to a stop in the "gravel," waits for a second, then is placed back on the track at zero speed.

JavaScript
/** * F1 SLOT CARS - "CRASH & RECOVERY" EDITION
 * P1: 'W' | P2/AI: 'UP_ARROW'
 * Warning: Don't take corners at full throttle!
 */

let gameState = "START";
let numPlayers = 1;
let trackPoints = [];
let cars = [];
let telemetryUI = [];

function setup() {
  createCanvas(800, 600);
  
  trackPoints = [
    {x: 150, y: 500}, {x: 650, y: 500}, // Start Straight
    {x: 750, y: 400}, {x: 600, y: 350}, // Sector 1
    {x: 700, y: 200}, {x: 400, y: 100}, // Back Straight
    {x: 100, y: 100}, {x: 150, y: 250}, // Hairpin
    {x: 350, y: 350}, {x: 100, y: 400}  // Final Turn
  ];

  cars.push(new SlotCar("RED RACER", color(255, 50, 50), 87, false, -12)); 
  cars.push(new SlotCar("BLUE BOLT", color(50, 150, 255), UP_ARROW, true, 12));

  setupDOM();
}

function setupDOM() {

  container.style('top', '20px');
  container.style('right', '20px');
  container.style('font-family', 'sans-serif');

  });

  background(30);

  if (gameState === "START") {
    drawStartScreen();
  } else {
    drawTrack();
    
    cars.forEach((car, i) => {
      let isAI = (i === 1 && numPlayers === 1);

function drawTrack() {
  // Grass/Infield
  fill(20, 60, 20);
  noStroke();
  beginShape();
  for (let p of trackPoints) { vertex(p.x, p.y); }
  endShape(CLOSE);

  // Asphalt
  noFill();
  stroke(60);
  strokeWeight(50);
  beginShape();
  for (let p of trackPoints) { curveVertex(p.x, p.y); }
  endShape(CLOSE);

  // The Slot
  stroke(180, 180, 0);
  strokeWeight(2);
  beginShape();
  for (let p of trackPoints) { curveVertex(p.x, p.y); }
  endShape(CLOSE);
  
  // Finish Line
  stroke(255);
  strokeWeight(6);
  line(150, 475, 150, 525);
}

class SlotCar {
  constructor(name, col, controlKey, canBeAI, laneOffset) {
    this.name = name;
    this.col = col;
    this.key = controlKey;
    this.laneOffset = laneOffset;
    
    this.pos = createVector(0,0);
    this.angle = 0;
    this.progress = 0;
    this.speed = 0;
    this.topSpeed = 0;
    this.laps = 0;
    
    // Physics Constants
    this.maxSpeedConst = 0.007;
    this.accel = 0.00018;
    this.friction = 0.98;
    
    // Crash State
    this.isCrashed = false;
    this.crashPos = createVector(0,0);
    this.crashVel = createVector(0,0);
    this.crashTimer = 0;
  }

  update(activeAI) {
    if (this.isCrashed) {
      this.updateCrash();
      return;
    }

    let driving = activeAI ? this.runAI() : keyIsDown(this.key);

    if (driving) {
      this.speed += this.accel;
    } else {
      this.speed *= this.friction;
    }

    this.speed = constrain(this.speed, 0, this.maxSpeedConst);
    
    // Calculate Curvature (for crash logic)
    let p1 = this.getPointAt(this.progress);
    let p2 = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.002);
    let p3 = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.004);
    
    let v1 = createVector(p2.x - p1.x, p2.y - p1.y);
    let v2 = createVector(p3.x - p2.x, p3.y - p2.y);
    let deltaAngle = abs(v1.angleBetween(v2));

    // CRASH CONDITION: Speed * Sharpness of turn
    if (this.speed * deltaAngle > 0.0018) {
      this.triggerCrash(p1, v1);
      return;
    }

    this.progress += this.speed;

    // Telemetry
    let curKmh = floor(this.speed * 45000);
    if (curKmh > this.topSpeed) this.topSpeed = curKmh;

    if (this.progress >= 1) {
      this.progress = 0;
      this.laps++;
    }
  }

  runAI() {
    // AI scans ahead for corners
    let p1 = this.getPointAt(this.progress);
    let p2 = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.02); // Look ahead
    let p3 = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.04);
    let v1 = createVector(p2.x - p1.x, p2.y - p1.y);
    let v2 = createVector(p3.x - p2.x, p3.y - p2.y);
    let upcomingCurvature = abs(v1.angleBetween(v2));

    // Brake if a sharp turn is coming, otherwise floor it
    if (upcomingCurvature > 0.15 && this.speed > 0.003) return false;
    return this.speed < 0.005;
  }

  triggerCrash(pos, heading) {
    this.isCrashed = true;
    this.crashPos = createVector(pos.x, pos.y);
    this.crashVel = heading.setMag(this.speed * 800); 
    this.speed = 0;
    this.crashTimer = 120; // 2 seconds at 60fps
  }

  updateCrash() {
    this.crashPos.add(this.crashVel);
    this.crashVel.mult(0.95); // Skid friction
    this.crashTimer--;

    if (this.crashTimer <= 0) {
      this.isCrashed = false;
      // Reset on track at current progress
    }
  }

  display() {
    let x, y, angle;

    if (this.isCrashed) {
      x = this.crashPos.x;
      y = this.crashPos.y;
      angle = this.crashVel.heading();
    } else {
      let pos = this.getPointAt(this.progress);
      let nextPos = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.001);
      x = pos.x;
      y = pos.y;
      angle = atan2(nextPos.y - y, nextPos.x - x);
    }

    push();
    translate(x, y);
    rotate(angle);
    if (!this.isCrashed) translate(0, this.laneOffset);

    // Flash if recovering
    if (this.isCrashed && this.crashTimer < 30 && frameCount % 10 < 5) {
       // invisible
    } else {
      fill(this.isCrashed ? color(100) : this.col);
      rectMode(CENTER);
      rect(0, 0, 28, 14, 3);
      fill(20);
      rect(-10, 0, 6, 18); // Wing
      fill(255, 150);
      rect(5, 0, 8, 8, 2); // Cockpit
    }
    pop();
  }

  getPointAt(t) {
    t = (t + 1) % 1;
    let i = floor(t * trackPoints.length);
    let p0 = trackPoints[(i + trackPoints.length - 1) % trackPoints.length];
    let p1 = trackPoints[i];
    let p2 = trackPoints[(i + 1) % trackPoints.length];
    let p3 = trackPoints[(i + 2) % trackPoints.length];
    let segmentT = (t * trackPoints.length) - i;
    return {
      x: curvePoint(p0.x, p1.x, p2.x, p3.x, segmentT),
      y: curvePoint(p0.y, p1.y, p2.y, p3.y, segmentT)
    };
  }
}

function updateTelemetry(index) {

  let status = car.isCrashed ? "<span style='color:yellow'>CRASHED!</span>" : "RACING";
  telemetryUI[index].html(`

class SlotCar {
  constructor(name, col, controlKey, laneOffset) {
    this.name = name;
    this.col = col;
    this.key = controlKey;
    this.laneOffset = laneOffset;
    
    this.progress = 0;
    this.speed = 0;
    this.topSpeed = 0;
    this.laps = 0;
    
    this.maxSpeedConst = 0.007;
    this.accel = 0.00018;
    this.friction = 0.98;
    
    this.isCrashed = false;
    this.crashPos = createVector(0,0);
    this.crashVel = createVector(0,0);
    this.crashTimer = 0;
  }

  update(activeAI) {
    if (this.isCrashed) {
      this.crashPos.add(this.crashVel);
      this.crashVel.mult(0.96);
      this.crashTimer--;
      if (this.crashTimer <= 0) this.isCrashed = false;
      return;
    }

    let driving = activeAI ? this.runAI() : keyIsDown(this.key);
    this.speed = driving ? this.speed + this.accel : this.speed * this.friction;
    this.speed = constrain(this.speed, 0, this.maxSpeedConst);
    
    // Physics check for turns
    let p1 = this.getPointAt(this.progress);
    let p2 = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.002);
    let p3 = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.004);
    let v1 = createVector(p2.x - p1.x, p2.y - p1.y);
    let v2 = createVector(p3.x - p2.x, p3.y - p2.y);
    
    if (this.speed * abs(v1.angleBetween(v2)) > 0.0019) {
      this.isCrashed = true;
      this.crashPos = createVector(p1.x, p1.y);
      this.crashVel = v1.setMag(this.speed * 700);
      this.crashTimer = 100;
      this.speed = 0;
      return;
    }

    this.progress += this.speed;
    if (floor(this.speed * 45000) > this.topSpeed) this.topSpeed = floor(this.speed * 45000);
    if (this.progress >= 1) { this.progress = 0; this.laps++; }
  }

  runAI() {
    let p1 = this.getPointAt(this.progress);
    let p2 = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.03);
    let p3 = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.06);
    let curv = abs(createVector(p2.x-p1.x, p2.y-p1.y).angleBetween(createVector(p3.x-p2.x, p3.y-p2.y)));
    return (curv > 0.18 && this.speed > 0.0035) ? false : this.speed < 0.0055;
  }

  display() {
    let x, y, angle;
    if (this.isCrashed) {
      x = this.crashPos.x; y = this.crashPos.y; angle = this.crashVel.heading();
    } else {
      let pos = this.getPointAt(this.progress);
      let next = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.001);
      x = pos.x; y = pos.y; angle = atan2(next.y - y, next.x - x);
    }

    push();
    translate(x, y);
    rotate(angle);
    if (!this.isCrashed) translate(0, this.laneOffset);
    
    fill(this.isCrashed ? 100 : this.col);
    rectMode(CENTER);
    rect(0, 0, 26, 12, 3); // Main body
    fill(20);
    rect(-10, 0, 4, 16); // Wing
    fill(255, 180);
    rect(4, 0, 6, 6, 2); // Glass
    pop();
  }

  getPointAt(t) {
    t = (t + 1) % 1;
    let i = floor(t * trackPoints.length);
    let p0 = trackPoints[(i + trackPoints.length - 1) % trackPoints.length];
    let p1 = trackPoints[i];
    let p2 = trackPoints[(i + 1) % trackPoints.length];
    let p3 = trackPoints[(i + 2) % trackPoints.length];
    return {
      x: curvePoint(p0.x, p1.x, p2.x, p3.x, (t * trackPoints.length) - i),
      y: curvePoint(p0.y, p1.y, p2.y, p3.y, (t * trackPoints.length) - i)
    };
  }
}

      this.crashVel.mult(0.95); // Skid to a halt
      this.crashTimer--;
      if (this.crashTimer <= 0) this.isCrashed = false; // Recovery
      return;
    }

    let driving = isAI ? this.runAI() : keyIsDown(this.key);
    this.speed = driving ? this.speed + 0.0002 : this.speed * 0.97;
    this.speed = constrain(this.speed, 0, 0.008);

    // CRASH SENSOR: Calculate turn sharpness (delta angle)
    let p1 = this.getPointAt(this.progress);
    let p2 = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.005);
    let v1 = createVector(p2.x - p1.x, p2.y - p1.y);
    let v2 = createVector(this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.01).x - p2.x, this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.01).y - p2.y);
    let turnSharpness = abs(v1.angleBetween(v2));

    // Threshold: Speed * Sharpness. If high, you fly!
    if (this.speed * turnSharpness > 0.0008) {
      this.isCrashed = true;
      this.crashPos = createVector(p1.x, p1.y);
      this.crashVel = v1.setMag(this.speed * 1000); 
      this.crashTimer = 120; // 2 second penalty
      this.speed = 0;
      return;
    }

    this.progress += this.speed;
    if (floor(this.speed * 45000) > this.topSpeed) this.topSpeed = floor(this.speed * 45000);
    if (this.progress >= 1) { this.progress = 0; this.laps++; }
  }

  runAI() {
    let p1 = this.getPointAt(this.progress);
    let p2 = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.05);
    let curv = abs(createVector(p2.x-p1.x, p2.y-p1.y).angleBetween(createVector(this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.1).x-p2.x, this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.1).y-p2.y)));
    return (curv > 0.12 && this.speed > 0.004) ? false : this.speed < 0.006;
  }

  display() {
    let x, y, angle;
    if (this.isCrashed) {
      x = this.crashPos.x; y = this.crashPos.y; angle = this.crashVel.heading();
    } else {
      let pos = this.getPointAt(this.progress);
      let next = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.001);
      x = pos.x; y = pos.y; angle = atan2(next.y - y, next.x - x);
    }

    push();
    translate(x, y); rotate(angle);
    if (!this.isCrashed) translate(0, this.laneOffset);
    
    noStroke();
    fill(this.isCrashed ? 100 : this.col); // Body Color (Red or Blue)
    rectMode(CENTER);
    rect(0, 0, 30, 15, 4); 
    fill(20); rect(-12, 0, 5, 20); // Wing
    fill(255, 200); rect(5, 0, 8, 8, 2); // Glass
    pop();
  }

  getPointAt(t) {
    t = (t + 1) % 1;
    let i = floor(t * trackPoints.length);
    let p = [trackPoints[(i + trackPoints.length - 1) % trackPoints.length], trackPoints[i], trackPoints[(i + 1) % trackPoints.length], trackPoints[(i + 2) % trackPoints.length]];
    return { x: curvePoint(p[0].x, p[1].x, p[2].x, p[3].x, (t * trackPoints.length) - i), y: curvePoint(p[0].y, p[1].y, p[2].y, p[3].y, (t * trackPoints.length) - i) };
  }
}

function updateTelemetry(i) {
  let c = cars[i];
  let cStr = i === 0 ? "#ff4444" : "#44aaff";
  telemetryUI[i].html(`<b style="color:${cStr}">${c.name}</b><br>LAP: ${c.laps} | KM/H: ${floor(c.speed * 45000)}<br>${c.isCrashed ? '<span style="color:yellow">STATUS: CRASHED</span>' : 'STATUS: OK'}`);

  constructor(name, col, key, laneOffset) {

    this.progress = 0; this.speed = 0; this.topSpeed = 0; this.laps = 0;
    this.isCrashed = false; this.crashPos = createVector(0,0); this.crashVel = createVector(0,0);
    this.crashTimer = 0;

      this.crashPos.add(this.crashVel);
      this.crashVel.mult(0.96);
      this.crashTimer--;
      if (this.crashTimer <= 0) {
        this.isCrashed = false;
        this.speed = 0;
      }
      return;

      this.speed += this.accelPower;
    } else {
      this.speed *= this.friction;
    }

    let p2 = this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.005);
    let v1 = createVector(p2.x - p1.x, p2.y - p1.y);
    let v2 = createVector(this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.01).x - p2.x, this.getPointAt(this.progress + 0.01).y - p2.y);
